The paper discusses information measures and secret key rates, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-fields of computer science. The use of triangle inequality suggests a possible connection to geometric methods in computer science (cs.DS). The discussion of implications of the conjecture may involve applications in multimedia (cs.MM) and social networks (cs.SI).
